Fall Creek first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2020 U.S. census]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Geography Changes|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs/technical-documentation/table-and-geography-changes/2020/geography-changes.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=}}</ref>

As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US1725245 |access-date=2022-06-28 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> there were 31 people, 14 households, and 14 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{Convert|563.64|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 12 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|218.18|/sqmi|/km2}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 93.55% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 3.23% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 3.23% from two or more races.

